verbose_text: The dopamine transporter (DAT), which is one of the targets of amphetamine, is highly expressed in the dorsolateral striatum, and less expressed in more medial and ventral regions of the striatum and in the pre-frontal cortex, where Catechol-O-methyl transferase (COMT) is more prevalent.
